      "content": {
        "title": "Lisfranc and Midfoot Injuries — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Tarsometatarsal joint complex injuries from direct or indirect force causing instability of the midfoot arch.",
        "summary": "Missed Lisfranc injuries cause chronic pain and collapse. ORIF versus primary fusion depends on instability pattern."
      },
